text: Macrothyatira labiata is a moth in the family Drepanidae first described by Max Gaede in 1930. It is found in Myanmar, China (Sichuan, Yunnan) and Thailand. The Global Lepidoptera Names Index has this name as a synonym of Macrothyatira oblonga. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1930 Category:Thyatirinae Category:Moths of Asia
title: Macrothyatira labiata
